#### Q66. Both const and @JvmField create constants. What can @JvmField do that const cannot?

```kotlin
class Styles {
  companion object {
    const val COLOR = "Blue"
      @JvmField val SIZE = "Really big"
   }
}
```

- %OPTION% `const` works only with strings and primitives. `@JvmField` does not have that restriction.
- %OPTION% `@JvmField` works as a top-level variable, but `const` works only in a class.
- %OPTION% `@JvmField` is compatible with Java, but `const` is not.
- %OPTION% `@JvmField` is always inlined for faster code.

[reference](https://github.com/ythy/blog/issues/328)

