#### Q70. What will happen when you try to build and run this code snippet?

```kotlin
class SpecialFunction : () -> Unit {
  override fun invoke() {
    println("Invoked from an instance.")
  }
}
fun main() {
  try { SpecialFunction()() }
  catch (ex: Exception) { println("An error occurred") }
}
```

- %OPTION% A syntax error occurs due to the line `SpecialFunction()()`.
- %OPTION% The message "An Error occurred" is displayed.
- %OPTION% The message "Invoked from an instance." is displayed. // the second "()" is equals to .invoke()
- %OPTION% A compile error occurs. You cannot override the `invoke()` method.
